content.content: For repositories owned by me, remove my stars if they have also been starred by other users.

To proceed with this task, I will retrieve the information about the currently authenticated GitHub account, including the starred repositories. Then I will check each starred repository to see if it has been starred by other users. If so, I will remove the star from those repositories. Here's the structured code for this process:

```python
# Get information for the currently authenticated GitHub account
github_user_info = get_logged_in_github_user_information()

# Retrieve starred repositories
starred_repositories = github_user_info.get("starred_repositories", [])

# Iterate over each starred repository
for repo_name in starred_repositories:
    # Get information about the repository
    repo_info = get_github_repository_information(repo_name)
    # Check if it is starred by other users
    if repo_info.get("stars") > 1: # Assuming "stars" gives the count of stars by all users
        # Unstar the repository
        git_unstar(repo_name)
```
